# Add New Instance Families to EC2 Sweet Spot Study

## Goal Description
Extend the existing study to include AWS **Compute Optimized (C5)** and **General Purpose (M5)** instance families, as requested by reviewers. This involves updating benchmarking scripts to support these families and refactoring the scaling analysis script to be generic and reusable for any instance type.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Cost Implication:** Running benchmarks on new families (C5, M5) will incur additional AWS costs. Please review the instance list and ensure budget is available.
> **CPU Verification:** For new families, the strict CPU homogeneity check will be set to "Log Only" initially, as we do not yet know the dominant CPU model for these instances in `us-east-1a`.

